<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7609> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7609" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See MRR, Index, 2.570. Cos. desig. for 29, but since another had occupied his place he was adlected by Augustus among the consulares in that year (Dio 42.4; cf. 54.4.5, governor in Spain). See PIR(2) F 590; Wiseman, NM 233, no. 188.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6409> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6409" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Asia under Antony (note the title Legatus in Liv. Per. 131). He organized forces to oppose Sextus Pompey's invasion of his province until Titius came at Antony's command, and refused Pompey's offer to surrender to him personally (App. BC 5.137-142; Dio 49.17-18; Oros. 6.19.2, Antonianis ducibus). See PIR² 3.232, no. 590; De Laet no. 183." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6373> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6373" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Asia (no title preserved) in 36 and 35, when Sextus Pompey came to the East (App. BC 5.137; Dio 49.17.5; see 35, Promagistrates). See PIR² 3.232, no. 590; De Laet no. 183." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6310> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6310" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Antony to bring the four legions from Africa which were formerly under T. Sextius (App. BC 5.75)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6283> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6283" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Envoy of Lucius Antonius, with two others, to Octavian to negotiate the surrender of Perusia (App. BC 5.40-41). See PIR² 3.232, no. 590; De Laet no. 183." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6251> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6251" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A supporter of Lucius Antony, who commanded the garrison of Sentinum before its capture by Salvidienus Rufus (App. BC 5.30; Dio 48.13.6). See 40, Legates; PIR² 3.232, no. 590; De Laet no. 183." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6148> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6148" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A candidate in 43 (Cic. Fam. 10.25, and 26), who would probably go on to the office with Plancus' support. See PIR² 3.232, no. 590." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6108> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6108" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate under Munatius Plancus in Transalpine Gaul (Cic. Fam. 10.11.3) who was sent on several occasions to bring reports to the Senate and to Cicero (Cic. Fam. 10.6.1, and 8.5, with title, and 10.1, and 12.1), and also to Octavian (10.24.7). Cicero urged him not to compete for a praetorship prematurely (Cic. Fam. 10.25, and 26). See 44, Legates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6015> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6015" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably a Legate under Munatius Plancus in Gaul in 44 (Cic. Fam. 10. 1.4; see 43, Legates), and a frequent Envoy and messenger to Rome (Cic. Fam. 10.3, and 4. 1). See PIR² 3.232, no. 590." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5448> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5448" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cicero relied on him particularly to prevent the prorogation of his provincial command (Cic. Att. 5.2.1, and 18.3; 6.1.11; Cael. in Cic. Fam. 8.10.3, and 11.2; Cic. Fam. 15.14.5). See PIR² 3.232, no. 590." .
